  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Revision total hip replacement arthroplasty is a surgery having intra- and postoperative
      substantial blood loss. The investigators will investigate the relationship between the
      various hematologic variables and postoperative bleeding volume.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
